.card-header.orange-background Install Ubuntu Touch on the #{data.name}
.card-body
  #bootloaderDefinitelyLocked(hidden='hidden', style="margin-bottom: 15px")
    .row.align-items-center
      .col.col
        .text(style="margin-bottom: 15px") #[b Note]: Unfortunately the #{data.name}'s Bootloader can not be unlocked if the device was sold with Android. That means, that Ubuntu Touch can #[b only] be installed on the #{data.name} Ubuntu Edition, #[b not on the Android version]!
        .text There is not a lot we can do about that, and luckily most devices do not have that restriction. If you are the proud owner of a #{data.name} Ubuntu Edition, you are not affected by this, and you can simply use the UBports Installer to switch to the UBports version of Ubuntu Touch.
  #bootloaderLocked(hidden='hidden', style="margin-bottom: 15px")
    .row.align-items-center
      .col.col
        .text(style="margin-bottom: 15px") #[b Note]: Unfortunately the #{data.name}'s Bootloader is locked while the device is running Android. That means that you will have to #[a(href="https://docs.ubports.com/en/latest/userguide/install.html#install-on-legacy-android-devices") install the manufacturer's Ubuntu image] before you can switch to the latest Ubuntu Touch release using the UBports Installer.
        .text This is just a small annoyance, but it's #[a(href="https://docs.ubports.com/en/latest/userguide/install.html#install-on-legacy-android-devices") not difficult] and luckily most devices do not have that restriction. Also, if you are the proud owner of a #{data.name} Ubuntu Edition, you are not affected by this, and you can simply use the UBports Installer to switch to the UBports version of Ubuntu Touch.
  .row.align-items-center
    .col.col
      img.item-center.wide-img.rounded.shadow(src="/img/ubpi.jpg", 
      style="min-width: 200px; margin-bottom: 15px")
    .col.col
      .text With the #[a(href="", data-toggle="modal" data-target="#installerModal") UBports Installer], you can get Ubuntu Touch on your #{data.name} without breaking a sweat. You can use any Linux, Windows, or macOS computer to run the installer. Simply plug in your device and follow the on-screen instructions, then sit back and let the computer do all the work for you. Alternatively, you can follow the #[a(href="", data-toggle="modal" data-target="#manualInstallationModal") manual installation instructions].
      .text-center(style="margin-top: 15px")
        a.button.btn.btn-primary.btn-xl.orange-background(href="", data-toggle="modal" data-target="#installerModal") Install Ubuntu Touch
  .row.align-items-center
    .col.col
      div(style="margin-top: 20px;" class="aspect-ratio")
        iframe(width="854" height="480" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/zuLFTGkuD68?autoplay=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen)
